Quote: His work on the silicified rocks plainly pointed the way to a theory of metasomatic replacement of country by vein-material. [fn] The term `country rock', now so commonly employed by writers on economic geology, is, strictly speaking, tautological. The miners of the Hauraki Goldfield, as a rule, employ the more correct expression, `country'.
